    lesson: 'The "limited authority" or "missing authority" tactic uses an absent, unmovable decision-maker to harden a position and resist concessions. Whether the constraint is real or staged, the move is the same: probe it. Ask what the approver would need to say yes, request that they join, or get the criteria in writing. This tests whether the limit is genuine and often reopens the room the tactic tried to close.',
