    lesson: 'Negotiation power flows mainly from alternatives. A strong BATNA means you can walk and still be fine, which lets you hold firm, decline bad terms, and credibly resist pressure. Personal style, talk time, and organizational size are weak or unreliable substitutes. The highest-leverage preparation is often improving your real outside options before you ever sit down.',
