    lesson: 'Because professional life is built on repeated and interconnected dealings, your reputation is an asset that survives any single negotiation. A counterpart caught in bad faith pays in reduced trust, harder future negotiations, lost referrals, and information that travels. Treating each deal as one-shot ignores this; the reputational shadow of the future is a powerful, self-interested reason to bargain hard but honestly.',
