    lesson: 'A mandate memo is the internal agreement that authorizes a negotiator: it states the objectives, the limits of their authority (what they can and cannot commit to), and the conditions under which they should walk away. It protects against the principal-agent gap — promising terms the organization will not honor — and gives the negotiator clear guardrails. It is about your own side\'s authority, distinct from analyzing the counterpart.',
    source,
