    lesson: 'A caucus is a private, confidential meeting between the facilitator (or mediator) and one party, away from the others. It lets people drop their public posturing, reveal real interests and constraints, test options, and cool down — information that is hard to surface when everyone is performing for the room. Caucuses are exploratory and temporary; binding decisions return to the joint table.',
