    lesson: 'A durable agreement is one that both sides can actually implement within their real authority, resources, and incentives, with obligations clear enough that performance is verifiable and a path for resolving disputes. Fragile agreements are those rushed past objections, extracted lopsidedly, or left strategically vague — each sets up resistance, reinterpretation, or collapse at implementation. Optimize for what survives the day after signing.',
